    MOD = 10 ** 9 - 7
    N = 1 << X + Y + Z
    NX = 1 << X
    NY = 1 << X + Y
    NZ = 1 << X + Y + Z
    MX = (1 << X) - 1
    MY = (1 << Y + X) - (1 << X)
    MZ = (1 << X + Y + Z) - (1 << Y + X)
    MMX = MX << 1
    MMY = MY << 1
    MMZ = MZ << 1
    dp = [0] * N
    dp[1] = 1
    for _ in range(n):
        ndp = [0] * N
        for mask in range(N):
            if dp[mask] == 0:
                continue
            mx = mask & MX
            my = mask & MY
            mz = mask & MZ
            for j in range(1, 11):
                nmx = mx << j
                nmx &= MMX
                nmy = my << j
                nmy &= MMY
                nmz = mz << j
                nmz &= MMZ
                nmask = nmx | nmy | nmz | 1
                if not nmask & 1 << X + Y + Z:
                    ndp[nmask] += dp[mask]
                    ndp[nmask] %= MOD
        dp = ndp
    total_sequences = pow(10, n, MOD)
    valid_sequences = sum(dp) % MOD
    return (total_sequences - valid_sequences) % MOD
